      {
        "title": "Swordsage",
        "excerpt": "Swordsages are mystical fighters who perform supernatural feats of martial ability. They often fight in melee, but many swordsages try to avoid the front lines. Swordsages’ supernatural abilities come from their innate ki powers, which they might have unlocked through years of meditation and training.   Swordsage talents produce a variety of supernatural effects without relying on formal arcane magic. Their talents might create mirages of multiple attacks, turn the swordsage incorporeal as they dodge, or shape their ki into solid objects. Swordsage ribbons use ki for minor utility effects.   Examples of swordsages in fiction include almost all anime fighters that have supernatural abilities, as well as some high fantasy magic swordsmen and wuxia heroes.     Powers          Name     Tier     Type     Description                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      Elemental Weapon                  Novice                                                              You enhance your weapon with damaging elemental energy                                               Ki Blast                  Novice                                                              You blast enemies with a bolt of concentated ki energy                                               Ki Pool                  Novice                                      You have a pool of ki points that fuel your Swordsage powers                                               Mind over Body                  Novice                                                              You resist a physical attack through pure mental fortitude                                               Spirit Carve                  Novice                                                              You strike directly at your enemy’s soul, bypassing their defense                                               Sword Flight                  Veteran                                                              You can levitate above the ground by flying on your sword                                               Battle Aura                  Ribbon                                                              You unleash your battle aura, glowing bright with power                                               Perfect Meditation                  Ribbon                                      You can enter a mediatative trance instead of eating or sleeping                                               Ultimate Technique                  Ribbon                                                              You announce the name of your latest ultimate technique                                                                                          Talents                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  Elemental Weapon                                   Novice                              Encounter                                Duration         Until the end of your next turn                  Choose one of the Acid, Cold, Electricity, Fire, or Force traits. Your melee Strikes deal an extra 1d6 damage of the chosen trait on a success.                                           Ki Blast                                   Novice                              Attack              Force                                Range         120 feet                  Make a Spirit attack roll against your target’s Defense.                       Critical Success         Your target takes 2d10 + Spirit damage                   Success         Your target takes 1d10 + Spirit damage                                                            Ki Pool                         Novice                                Prerequisites         Any Encounter Swordsage talent                  You have a Ki Pool that stores up to 3 Ki points. You can spend 1 Ki point at any time to refresh a Encounter Swordsage talent, letting you use it again without taking a 5-minute rest. Your Ki Pool replenishes when you complete an 8-hour rest.                                           Mind over Body                                   Novice                              Encounter                                Trigger         An attack targets you                  The attack’s DC is your Spirit DC + 5.                                           Spirit Carve                                   Novice                              Encounter               Make a melee Strike with a +5 bonus. The DC of this Strike is your target’s Spirit DC.                                           Sword Flight                                   Veteran                                Requirements         You are wielding a melee weapon              Duration         1 minute, until you use this power again, until you use any Attack power, or until you stop riding on the weapon                  You ride on your weapon and float into the air. You gain a Fly Speed equal to your Speed. You cannot fly more than 60 feet above the ground.                                                                                             Ribbons                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          Battle Aura                                   Ribbon                                Duration         1 minute, or until you decide to end this power                  You glow bright with power, shedding colorful light as a torch. You have advantage on Intimidate rolls to impress others with physical strength.         The color of your battle aura is specific to you as an individual.                                      Perfect Meditation                         Ribbon               You can enter a state of perfect meditation that replaces your need for food and rest. While meditating, you don’t need to eat or drink. You can also meditate instead of sleeping, gaining all the benefits of resting while remaining aware of the outside world. You can’t use powers while meditating.                                           Ultimate Technique                                   Ribbon                              Daily                                Trigger         You make a die roll                  You shout the name of your ultimate technique. You must come up with and declare this name out of character. If the name is at least 5 words, and if your character hasn’t used Ultimate Technique with the same name before, you have advantage on the die roll.",
        "url": "/swordsage.html"
      }
      
